cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a verification method based on logically constrained term rewriting systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with procedural programs and introduces an extension of transformation methods. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper aims to verify the correctness of programs. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper uses rewriting induction methods. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions verifying memory safety.
